# tkv2 — std/pwa extensions (cacheVersion, networkFirst, offlineHtml, maskableIcon)

Slice `tkv2-pwa-adopt` of `specs/ssc-toolkit-v2.md`. Registers the PWA routes
with the new offline-first parameters and asserts the generated manifest and
service worker carry them. Interpreter-only (the pwa plugin registers server
routes; there is no JS-lane server here).

```scalascript
pwa(
  name            = "Busi Test",
  shortName       = "busi",
  description     = "offline-first test app",
  themeColor      = "#0b0d10",
  backgroundColor = "#0b0d10",
  display         = "standalone",
  startUrl        = "/react",
  icons           = List("/icons/icon-192.png", "/icons/icon-512.png"),
  precache        = List("/react"),
  cacheVersion    = "v8",
  networkFirst    = List("/api/home", "/react"),
  offlineHtml     = "<h1>offline</h1>",
  maskableIcon    = "/icons/icon-512.png",
)

serveAsync(18631)

val manifest = httpGet("http://localhost:18631/manifest.json").body
println(manifest.contains("\"theme_color\":\"#0b0d10\""))
println(manifest.contains("\"start_url\":\"/react\""))
println(manifest.contains("\"sizes\":\"192x192\""))
println(manifest.contains("\"purpose\":\"maskable\""))

val sw = httpGet("http://localhost:18631/sw.js").body
println(sw.contains("ssc-pwa-v8"))
println(sw.contains("NETWORK_FIRST = [\"/api/home\", \"/react\"]"))
println(sw.contains("<h1>offline</h1>"))
println(sw.contains("mode === 'navigate'"))
```
